{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":758,"text":"In 2012, when I painted\nthe minaret of Jara Mosque"},{"time":5025,"text":"in my hometown of Gabés,\nin the south of Tunisia,"},{"time":7980,"text":"I never thought that graffiti would bring\nso much attention to a city."}]},{"cues":[{"time":13271,"text":"At the beginning, I was just looking\nfor a wall in my hometown,"},{"time":17221,"text":"and it happened that the minaret\nwas built in '94."},{"time":21102,"text":"And for 18 years, those 57 meters\nof concrete stayed grey."},{"time":26617,"text":"When I met the imam for the first time,\nand I told him what I wanted to do,"},{"time":30242,"text":"he was like, \"Thank God you finally came,\""},{"time":32710,"text":"and he told me that for years\nhe was waiting for somebody"},{"time":35541,"text":"to do something on it."},{"time":37422,"text":"The most amazing thing about this imam\nis that he didn't ask me anything --"},{"time":41532,"text":"neither a sketch,\nor what I was going to write."}]},{"cues":[{"time":45959,"text":"In every work that I create,\nI write messages"},{"time":48856,"text":"with my style of calligraffiti --\na mix of calligraphy and graffiti."},{"time":53622,"text":"I use quotes or poetry."},{"time":56153,"text":"For the minaret, I thought that\nthe most relevant message"},{"time":58884,"text":"to be put on a mosque\nshould come from the Quran,"},{"time":61524,"text":"so I picked this verse:"},{"time":63159,"text":"\"Oh humankind, we have created you\nfrom a male and a female,"},{"time":66423,"text":"and made you people and tribe,\nso you may know each other.\""},{"time":69862,"text":"It was a universal call for peace,\ntolerance, and acceptance"},{"time":73203,"text":"coming from the side that we don't usually\nportray in a good way in the media."}]},{"cues":[{"time":77661,"text":"I was amazed to see how the local\ncommunity reacted to the painting,"},{"time":81453,"text":"and how it made them proud to see\nthe minaret getting so much attention"},{"time":85784,"text":"from international press\nall around the world."},{"time":89346,"text":"For the imam, it was not\njust the painting;"},{"time":91538,"text":"it was really deeper than that."},{"time":93427,"text":"He hoped that this minaret would become\na monument for the city,"},{"time":96888,"text":"and attract people\nto this forgotten place of Tunisia."},{"time":100759,"text":"The universality of the message,"},{"time":102933,"text":"the political context\nof Tunisia at this time,"},{"time":105203,"text":"and the fact that I was writing\nQuran in a graffiti way"},{"time":108711,"text":"were not insignificant."},{"time":110377,"text":"It reunited the community."}]},{"cues":[{"time":113559,"text":"Bringing people, future generations,\n"},{"time":116573,"text":"together through Arabic calligraphy"},{"time":119573,"text":"is what I do."},{"time":121082,"text":"Writing messages is\nthe essence of my artwork."},{"time":124896,"text":"What is funny, actually, is that\neven Arabic-speaking people"},{"time":128071,"text":"really need to focus a lot\nto decipher what I'm writing."},{"time":132668,"text":"You don't need to know\nthe meaning to feel the piece."},{"time":136012,"text":"I think that Arabic script touches\nyour soul before it reaches your eyes."},{"time":139757,"text":"There is a beauty in it\nthat you don't need to translate."},{"time":143628,"text":"Arabic script speaks to anyone, I believe;"},{"time":145930,"text":"to you, to you, to you, to anybody,"},{"time":149471,"text":"and then when you get the meaning,\n"},{"time":151431,"text":"you feel connected to it."},{"time":153435,"text":"I always make sure to write messages"},{"time":155806,"text":"that are relevant to the place\nwhere I'm painting,"},{"time":158201,"text":"but messages that have\na universal dimension,"},{"time":161306,"text":"so anybody around the world\ncan connect to it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":164699,"text":"I was born and raised in France, in Paris,"},{"time":167050,"text":"and I started learning how to write\nand read Arabic when I was 18."},{"time":171560,"text":"Today I only write messages in Arabic."},{"time":175084,"text":"One of the reasons\nthis is so important to me,"},{"time":178305,"text":"is because of all the reaction that\nI've experienced all around the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":183700,"text":"In Rio de Janeiro, I translated\nthis Portuguese poem"},{"time":187630,"text":"from Gabriela Tôrres Barbosa,"},{"time":189566,"text":"who was giving an homage\nto the poor people of the favela,"},{"time":192970,"text":"and then I painted it on the rooftop."},{"time":195367,"text":"The local community were really\nintrigued by what I was doing,"},{"time":198304,"text":"but as soon as I gave them\nthe meaning of the calligraphy,"},{"time":201921,"text":"they thanked me, as they felt\nconnected to the piece."}]},{"cues":[{"time":206723,"text":"In South Africa, in Cape Town,"},{"time":208737,"text":"the local community of Philippi"},{"time":211810,"text":"offered me the only\nconcrete wall of the slum."},{"time":214881,"text":"It was a school, and I wrote on it"},{"time":217278,"text":"a quote from Nelson Mandela,"},{"time":218770,"text":"saying, \"[in Arabic],\""},{"time":221457,"text":"which means, \"It seems\nimpossible until it's done.\""},{"time":224489,"text":"Then this guy came to me and said,\n\"Man, why you don't write in English?\""},{"time":228098,"text":"and I replied to him, \"I would consider\nyour concern legit if you asked me"},{"time":232217,"text":"why I didn't write in Zulu.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":234912,"text":"In Paris, once, there was this event,"},{"time":237080,"text":"and someone gave his wall to be painted."},{"time":242016,"text":"And when he saw I was painting in Arabic,"},{"time":244397,"text":"he got so mad -- actually, hysterical --\nand he asked for the wall to be erased."},{"time":248445,"text":"I was mad and disappointed."},{"time":250436,"text":"But a week later, the organizer\nof the event asked me to come back,"},{"time":254337,"text":"and he told me that there was a wall\nright in front of this guy's house."},{"time":258079,"text":"So, this guy --"},{"time":259255,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":261498,"text":"like, was forced to see it every day."},{"time":263547,"text":"At the beginning, I was going\nto write, \"[In Arabic],\""},{"time":266555,"text":"which means, \"In your face,\" but --"},{"time":268570,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":270937,"text":"I decided to be smarter\nand I wrote, \"[In Arabic],\""},{"time":274620,"text":"which means, \"Open your heart.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":277095,"text":"I'm really proud of my culture,"},{"time":280195,"text":"and I'm trying to be an ambassador\nof it through my artwork."},{"time":285734,"text":"And I hope that I can break\nthe stereotypes we all know,"},{"time":290694,"text":"with the beauty of Arabic script."},{"time":293207,"text":"Today, I don't write the translation\nof the message anymore on the wall."},{"time":299148,"text":"I don't want the poetry\nof the calligraphy to be broken,"},{"time":302849,"text":"as it's art and you can appreciate it\nwithout knowing the meaning,"},{"time":306054,"text":"as you can enjoy any music\nfrom other countries."},{"time":309630,"text":"Some people see that\nas a rejection or a closed door,"},{"time":313429,"text":"but for me, it's more an invitation --"},{"time":315922,"text":"to my language,\nto my culture, and to my art."}]},{"cues":[{"time":319225,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":320407,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}